                                            <p>Some of these are good information and helpful, some are a bit on the obvious side (sleep with correct posture to avoid back problems), and some are downright wrong. Apples and strawberries most definitely are NOT negative calorie foods for example. Your taste buds should tell you this, do you really think you wouldn't gain weight if you ate a whole bunch of apples? As for the raw food diet, well, the only benefit that it gives you (and in fact there are many foods that will not release most of their nutrition unless cooked) is to force the issue on whether or not you eat processed food. Raw food in and of itself has no more intrinsic food value than the same food with heat applied.</p>                                    </div>
